#: 3787
msgid "\"I won't do it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49453
msgid ""
"You see a tall, striking woman. She stands staring at the walls of the "
"tavern without seeing them, her hands slowly curling into fists and "
"unclenching. When she sees you, her eyes dart across your clothing and gear, "
"and then back to your eyes; a sardonic smile crosses her face, and she looks "
"away again."
msgstr ""

#: 49454
msgid "\"Greetings.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49455
msgid "Pass on."
msgstr ""

#: 49456
msgid ""
"She looks back at you and scowls. \"Do you always make a habit of talking to "
"strangers?\" "
msgstr ""

#: 49457
msgid "\"If I need to ask them questions, then yes.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49458
msgid "\"Not usually, but I thought I'd talk to you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49459
msgid "\"No. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49460
msgid ""
"\"What a fascinating life you must lead to do such things. Sadly for you, "
"I'm busy. I'd appreciate being left alone.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49461
msgid "\"I just had a few questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49462
msgid "\"I'll just leave you alone, then. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49463
msgid ""
"\"What part of 'I'm busy' did you not understand? Leave... me... alone. "
"Thank you.\" She turns her attention back into herself, losing herself in "
"thought. She begins chewing on her lower lip, and beads of blood sprout from "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: 49464 49479
msgid "\"Farewell, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49465
msgid ""
"You see a tall, striking woman. She stands staring at the walls of the "
"tavern without seeing them, her hands slowly curling into fists and "
"unclenching. When she sees you, her eyes dart across your clothing and gear, "
"and then back to your eyes; a sardonic smile crosses her face, and she looks "
"away again. \"Looking for something, cutter?\" she says, still not looking "
"at you."
msgstr ""

#: 49466
msgid "\"I understand you're the next person I'm to talk to about this key.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49467
msgid "\"I had some questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49468
msgid "\"Not right now. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49469
msgid ""
"\"About the key, hm?\" She arches an eyebrow at you. \"You want to know what "
"you have to do for it, don't you? It's easy enough, friend. Interested? Of "
"course you are; you've come to talk to me about it. Are you ready to listen, "
"I guess, is the real question.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49471
msgid "\"Tell me what I have to do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49472 49495 49499 49514 49518 49522
msgid "\"Not yet. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49473 49485
msgid ""
"Kitla has assigned me the task of getting legacies from two men - "
"Crumplepunch and Kester - or of solving the squabble they're having. In "
"return for this, she'll give me the second part of the Key to see the deva."
msgstr ""

#: 49474
msgid ""
"\"There are two men here, named Crumplepunch and Kester. Crumplepunch is the "
"smith, Kester the distiller. They both owe me a *lot* of money. One of them "
"owes the other as well, though, and so neither of them is paying me. They're "
"arguing about an inheritance; get me the legacies they're holding on to. I "
"can bargain with them *very* effectively, then. Failing that, get them to "
"solve their problems with each other - or kill them - and I'll give you the "
"second part of the Key.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49478
msgid ""
"She gives you an arch look. \"Maybe we can talk when you've finished that "
"little mission, hm? Go run along now.\" She turns back to her drink."
msgstr ""

#: 49480
msgid "She smiles sweetly. \"Then you won't get the Key. Go on now.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49481 67753
msgid "\"Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49482
msgid ""
"\"You're back, hm? It turns out that I've a use for you after all. You help "
"me, I help you, and we all wind up happy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49483
msgid "\"What is it I have to do?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49484 49525 67755
msgid "\"Maybe later. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49486
msgid ""
"Her eyes gleam in the half-light of the tavern. \"Do you have anything for "
"me, scarred man?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49487
msgid "\"I have both their legacies here.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49488
msgid "\"I have Crumplepunch's legacy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49489
msgid "\"I have Kester's legacy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49490
msgid "\"Crumplepunch is dead.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49491
msgid "\"Kester is dead.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49492
msgid ""
"\"Really? Give them to me, and I'll give you the second part of the Key.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49493
msgid "\"Here you go.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49494 49513 49517
msgid "\"I'm still trying to work some angles. Give me a chance.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49496
msgid ""
"She takes them from you and laughs evilly. \"NOW let's see them tell me they "
"can't find a way to pay me.\" She tucks the legacies away into a pouch at "
"her belt. \"Are you ready for the second part of the key?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49497 49520
msgid "\"Yes. Tell me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49498 49521
msgid "\"Not yet. Answer some questions first.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49500
msgid ""
"She sighs. \"The money they owe me isn't coming any faster with you talking "
"to me. Go on... go get it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49501 67754
msgid "\"All right, then. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49502
msgid ""
"She concentrates for a moment, and her voice takes on another, deeper tone "
"as she intones these words: \"Here their Prison ordained in utter darkness..."
"\" She pauses, and speaks normally. \"For the third part of the Key, go talk "
"to Nabat over there.\" She yawns mightily. \"I'm exhausted. Take this, and "
"then leave me alone for a time. I need to think about my next step here. "
"Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49503
msgid "\"I just wanted to ask some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49504 49510
msgid "\"I wanted mage training.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49505
msgid ""
"I received the second part of the Key from Kitla. It was \"Here their Prison "
"ordained in utter darkness...\" I am to go speak to a man called Nabat next."
msgstr ""

#: 49506
msgid ""
"\"Come back sometime later. I have a little too much on my mind right now..."
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 49507
msgid "\"Can you train me as a mage?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49508
msgid ""
"She sighs. \"Look, I have a lot of planning to do with my future... let me "
"just give you the Key and we'll call it even, all right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49509 49524
msgid "\"All right. Give it to me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49511
msgid ""
"\"Are you going to give it to me?\" She holds out her hand. \"This'll make "
"sure Crumplepunch will find a way to pay me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49512 49516
msgid "\"Yes. Here you go.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49515
msgid ""
"\"Are you going to give it to me?\" She holds out her hand. \"This'll make "
"sure Kester will find a way to pay me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49519
msgid ""
"She tucks the legacy away into a pouch at her belt and smirks evilly. \"Do "
"you want the second part of the Key now?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49523
msgid ""
"She sighs. \"Thanks for solving this thing, but... look, I have a lot of "
"planning to do. Let me just give you the Key and we'll call it even, all "
"right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 50063
msgid "\"What was I supposed to do again?\""
msgstr ""

#: 6018
msgid "\"Will do. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66358
msgid "\"They're both dead.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66359
msgid "\"Nothing right now. I'm working on it. I had some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 66361
msgid ""
"\"You killed him? Just as well... that old goat was always pawing at me. Are "
"you ready for the second portion of the Key?\""
msgstr ""

#: 66362 66364 66366
msgid "\"Give it to me...\""
msgstr ""

#: 66363
msgid ""
"\"Good. I never could stand him. Are you ready for the second portion of the "
"Key?\""
msgstr ""

#: 66365
msgid ""
"\"Well, hello, killer! I didn't expect that, but I'm not entirely "
"disappointed, either. Are you ready for the second portion of the Key?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67738
msgid "Her eyes brighten. \"Oh? Have you studied the Art before?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67739
msgid "\"And you want to give up what you're doing now to renew your skills?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67740
msgid ""
"After some time talking about the Art, she nods her head and smiles. \"You "
"are truly gifted. You have all you need to travel down the mystic path again."
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 67741
msgid ""
"\"Let's first see if you even have the aptitude for it.\" She proceeds to "
"test your intelligence and reasoning ability with a long series of logic and "
"word puzzles..."
msgstr ""

#: 67742
msgid ""
"\"It looks like you have a functioning mind, at least.\" She studies you. "
"\"You've got a book, too. Good. You'll need that to write your spells in. "
"All spells need someplace for storage. They come in all shapes and sizes, "
"but in the end, they need to be written down for a mage to study. Are you "
"understanding this so far?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67743
msgid ""
"She keeps herself from laughing outright at you, but you can see a gleam of "
"contempt in her eyes. \"You haven't the mind necessary to be a mage. All "
"your spells would be like water in your mind, flowing out through your ears "
"before you could ever cast them. Stick with the sword, stick with thievery. "
"You'll never be good at spells.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67744
msgid ""
"\"Let's give you a little test, now. Take a look at this.\" She produces a "
"scroll. \"Read this, and tell me what it says.\" The glyphs on the scroll "
"squirm before your eyes, becoming meaningless."
msgstr ""

#: 67745
msgid ""
"Instinctively, you let your eyes relax and you take in the meaning of the "
"scroll almost subconsciously, as if another part of your brain had "
"reasserted itself. The scroll lists arcane syllables, spell components, "
"gestures, and rituals necessary for the completion of a spell."
msgstr ""

#: 67746
msgid ""
"Try as you might, you can't get the letters on the scroll to make sense to "
"you. Every time you think you've fixed the symbols in your mind, they swim "
"in your vision, leaving you with a pounding headache. Finally, after minutes "
"of intense scrutiny, you pull back from the parchment, your eyes glazing... "
"and suddenly the contents of the scroll are made clear. The scroll lists "
"arcane syllables, spell components, gestures, and rituals necessary for the "
"completion of a spell."
msgstr ""

#: 67747
msgid ""
"Kitla smirks. \"So you already know your way around a spell scroll, eh? What "
"that means is that you've had training sometime, even if you've forgotten "
"it, because only a mage could read the symbols on that scroll. You've opened "
"your mind to it again. You've just saved yourself years of study. "
"Congratulations.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67748
msgid ""
"\"You've already got the book, so all that's required now is that you know "
"how to memorize and cast your spells. First, you need to have a clear head "
"and plenty of rest before you can memorize spells. Before you rest, and this "
"is essential, choose the spells you want to memorize, and then relax. When "
"you awaken, spend some time with your written spells, and they'll enter into "
"your mind.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67749
msgid ""
"\"When you start out, your spells are limited. You'll be able to cast a "
"single spell, perhaps even as many as three. Use 'em well, because when "
"they're gone, you'll have to rest again before you can memorize more spells. "
"As you progress in the Art, though, you'll find your memory holds more and "
"more.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67750
msgid ""
"\"Once you cast a spell, it's erased from your memory. If you need to cast "
"the same spell twice, you'll need to memorize it twice.\" She pauses, "
"thinking. \"Keep a peery eye out for more spells. You can find them in many "
"different places and forms, from different people. When you do find them, "
"hoard them and put them in your spell book whenever possible. Just study "
"them carefully and write them down.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67751
msgid ""
"\"You've got it. Good. Here. Take these scrolls, and put them in your spell "
"book. Good luck.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67752
msgid "\"My thanks. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67756
msgid "\"Yes. I just need to brush up on some skills.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67757
msgid "\"No. I need instruction.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67758
msgid "\"Forget it. Just answer some questions.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67759
msgid "\"Forget it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67760
msgid "\"Yes.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67761
msgid "\"No, not really. Answer some questions instead...\""
msgstr ""

#: 67762
msgid "\"No, not really. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67763
msgid "\"Thanks. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67764 67765
msgid "Answer her questions as best you can."
msgstr ""

#: 67766
msgid "\"Yes. I need a book to write my spells in so I can study them later.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67767
msgid "\"Fine. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67768 67769
msgid "Examine the scroll."
msgstr ""

#: 67770 67771
msgid ""
"\"This is a minor divination, isn't it? Something to identify items for you."
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 67772
msgid "\"Thanks. What's the next step?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67773 67776 67778 67780
msgid "\"I think I've got the basics down. Let's get to training.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67774
msgid ""
"Kitla, the mage in the Traitor's Gate tavern in Curst, showed me a magic "
"scroll, and told me that my ability to read it meant that I had been a mage "
"at some point in my life. "
msgstr ""

#: 67775
msgid "\"How many spells can I cast?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67777
msgid "\"All right. Keep going.\""
msgstr ""

#: 67779
msgid "\"All right. Is that all?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67781
msgid ""
"Kitla taught me the fundamentals of magic. Before I rest, I'll need to pick "
"the spells I want to memorize by going to my spell book and choosing them. "
"If I want to be able to cast a spell multiple times, I'll have to memorize "
"the spell multiple times. Whenever I rest, I'll awake the next morning with "
"the spells in my memory, ready to be cast. I can only cast a small number of "
"spells each day until I become more proficient in their use."
msgstr ""
